  "body": "In my script:\r\n`eth.sendTransaction('0xFROM_ADDRESS',  null, amount)`\r\nInstead of raising error, have sent all amount to hell. Here is what generated instead of doing transaction:\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/tx/0x581b23337d023d40879e10cd94a138889b324c88e60158682febd3e19c1c27a5\r\nCreating a contract (especially dead one) for sendTransaction is unacceptable, and should be solved somehow to more reasonable action.\r\nLogging of my script is extensive, so I tracked every detail of this action. Here is piece of code executed:\r\n\r\n    winston.log('info', \"ETHSend: \", f, t, v);\r\n    web3.eth.sendTransaction({from: f, to: t, value: web3.toWei(v, \"ether\")},\r\n        function(err, result) {\r\n            if (err) {\r\n                winston.log('info', \"ETHSend error: \", err, result);\r\n                callback(null);\r\n                return;\r\n            }\r\n            winston.log('info', \"eth.sendTransaction: \", err, result);\r\n            session.txids.push({Currency: 'ETH', Amount: v,\r\n                CryptoAddress: t, TxId: result});\r\n            callback(null);\r\n        });\r\n\r\nBy the way, would some day be hardfork, so I recover my funds?\r\n\r\nI've lost 56 ETH total, check following TxHashes:\r\n0xaa2e6cc49535df058bcbd5ad153ff732b7540532a741dc0072822ea255b93748\r\n0x1871d172e87c974eccbaf4844a3c6748480192420e91074a82d05b74383d08cf\r\n0x2536d92cca7239c529413abe68b8a962bf35ab2c74c361f5974d117cf5b764f7\r\n0xe92704ec8689ac0ad459a057f340e9a6177447f441346139d5c881d314a8e481\r\n![zero_eth](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1641133/36278662-e68064bc-12ad-11e8-8af3-ad2eeb203bad.png)\r\n\r\ninstance=Geth/v1.7.2-stable-1db4ecdc/linux-amd64/go1.9",
