    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm sorry this happened to you, but it's an inherent feature of Ethereum transactions that there are two types of transactions: \r\n\r\n* Normal transactions: contains a `to` address\r\n* Contract-create transactions: does not contain a `to`-address. \r\n\r\nSo if you submit a transaction which does not contain a `to`, that is the result. So I would guess that the `t` is either `undefined` or `null` -- which you should see in your logs. ",
